<p>Spring is an active time for wildlife. Bears emerge from hibernation, elk move through the valleys, and migratory birds return. The Bow Valley Parkway and Vermilion Lakes are excellent for spring wildlife spotting. Keep your distance — bears with cubs are especially protective.</p>

<h2>Best Spring Activities</h2>
