<h2>Why the Water Is So Green</h2>
<p>Emerald Lake's colour comes from sunlight reflecting off the fine glacial rock flour (silt) suspended in the water. The particles are so fine they remain suspended for long periods and scatter green wavelengths of light. The lake is at its most vivid in July and August when glacial melt is highest.</p>

