<ul>
<li><strong>Elk:</strong> Herds frequently graze along the road and lakeshores, especially at dawn and dusk</li>
<li><strong>Bald eagles and ospreys:</strong> Nest and hunt near the lakes in summer. Watch for them perching in dead trees along the shore</li>
<li><strong>Beavers:</strong> Active at dawn and dusk. Look for their lodges and listen for the distinctive tail slap on water</li>
<li><strong>Muskrats:</strong> Commonly seen swimming in the marshier areas</li>
